<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,788,1055]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Diagnosis. Medusa with four or eight simple, unbranched perradial oral tentacles inserting at level of mouth rim; manubrial peduncle present; eight or exceptionally 16 marginal bulbs, each with one or more simple tentacles, usually with more tentacles on the perradial than the interradial bulbs; interradial medusa buds develop on manubrium; gonads encircling manubrium.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,788,1055]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">
